Package ntnu.idatt2001.ejhaslerjorgfi.model

Class Passage

java.lang.Object
ntnu.idatt2001.ejhaslerjorgfi.model.Passage
public class Passage extends Object

Passage

Definition

Represents a passage or an event which a Player may encounter during a game. It is an object acting as a section of the story plot. A Player may move from one Passage object to another through a Link.

Functionality

Passage objects may contain one or several Links to other Passages, providing the Player with the option to move to another Passage. Passages which has only a single Link to another Passage represents a linear story where each Passage or event must be encountered for the Player to proceed. Those Passages which contain Links to several other Passages are considered as non-linear stories, and the Player may choose its next Passage at will or be directed towards one based on the Players actions.

Attributes

A Passage contains a title which describes what event the Passage represents, as well as acting as an indetifier of the event.

The content field represents a text which acts as a paragraph or a dialogue in the story.

Passages also holds a collection of paths to other Passages in the links variable. It holds a list of Link objects, which the Passage contains, connecting the Passage to other Passages.
